cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.DL 

This paper analyzes the role of multilingual users in Wikipedia editing, which involves natural language processing and social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the study involves analyzing user behavior and patterns, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The study also involves analyzing the size and activity of different language editions, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
